{
  "stem": "2004.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I-- I managed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I managed to play soccer a little, play some other games with my-- with my peers.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I beg your pardon?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Primarily Jews.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were not peculiarly comfortable associating with our Polish Gentile friends.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We did not care to associate with them because they actually didn't want to associate with us either.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They called us all kinds of names.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was not a very congenial atmosphere.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We felt the anti-Semitic environment which was surrounding us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And furthermore, even in school the teachers, which were primarily Polish Gentile teachers, and to a great extent they made anti-Semitic remarks directed towards the Jews.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the usual.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Nothing very flattering towards the Jews-- dirty Jews, so on and so forth.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that, mind you, also came from a teacher.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And you could see a certain type of favoritism, which was extended towards the non-Jewish children as opposed to the Jewish children.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Whenever there was a fight which ensued between the Gentile boy and the Jewish boy, it was always the Jewish boy that was at fault, obviously.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we-- but we particularly didn't pay too much attention to it because as soon as school was over we went our way, and, of course, they went their way.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there was-- in our town, there was a-- there were incidences where young Jewish men-- by young Jewish men, I mean Jewish men in their late teens-- were attacked by students, by Gentile students.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they have organized sort of a self-defense.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we-- they have recruited-- of course, I was not part of it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was only-- at the time when the war broke out, I was only 12 years old.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But they have organized sort of a self-defense team.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
